Two Important Anniversaries of DPRK Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- Lectures and meetings were held in Chandigarh, India and Sofia and Bangkok from Dec. 11 to 16 on the occasion of the 14th anniversary of leader  Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 88th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk.
 The secretary general of the Asian Regional Institute of the Juche Idea said in a lecture that the vitality and attraction of the Juche idea fathered by President Kim Il Sung are increasing with each passing day, adding that many new organizations for the study of the Juche idea were formed in different countries and regions to intensify the activities for studying and disseminating the Juche idea worldwide. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun idea and politics are based on the Juche idea and fully meet the requirements of the Juche idea, he noted, and went on:
 The originality and vitality of the Songun idea and politics have been fully proven in the reality of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has achieved the perfect unity of the whole society with his politics of love and trust in the people, which meets the requirements of the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people will frustrate the U.S. imperialists' moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK and surely build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation by dint of their single-minded unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at a meeting held by the Bulgarian Group for the Study of the Juche Idea said that Kim Jong Il is the supreme commander with a high level of political ability and rare military quality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the undying exploits of Kim Jong Suk, they noted that Kim Jong Il has successfully carried forward the cause of Kim Il Sung as desired by her, thus defending the sovereignty of the country and steering the cause of global independence with his Songun politics to win the world fame as a great Songun brilliant commander.

Master's Degree Conferred on Korean in China 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- The degree of master of literature of the DPRK was conferred upon Ri Hae Yon, a student apprentice at the College of Literature of Kim Il Sung University.
 Ri discovered, put in order and comprehensively systematized the heritages of the advantageous national literature created by the Koreans on the basis of the Juche-oriented idea and theory of literature and art, thereby making a great contribution to the development of the history of novel literature of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An awarding ceremony was held at the People's Palace of Culture on Dec. 22. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Vice-Premier of the Cabinet Kwak Pom Gi who is chairman of the State Commission for Conferring Degrees and Titles of the DPRK, Kang Chun Gum, secretary general of the commission, and other officials concerned.

Functions of Youths and Students of DPRK Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- A meeting of youths and students was held at the Central Youth Hall on Dec. 22 to celebrate the 14th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army.
 At the meeting a report by Kim Kyong Ho, first secretary of the Central Committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League, was followed by speeches.
 The reporter and speakers said that holding Kim Jong Il at the top post of the revolutionary armed forces marked a historic event of weighty significance in the future development of the revolution and the accomplishment of the human cause of independence and it was the greatest fortune for the army and people of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that Kim Jong Il has put forward the People's Army as the main force of the revolution and strengthened and developed it to be invincible revolutionary armed forces strong in ideology and faith, they said that he has shown warm care for the young people so that they might glorify their worthy life with arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called upon all the young people to become Songun revolutionary comrades who staunchly safeguard the great Songun leadership exploits of Kim Jong Il and share destiny with him to the last and genuine vanguard fighters who devotedly defend the leader, protect the headquarters of the revolution politically and ideologically at the cost of their lives. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That day, a combined performance of winners of the art contests among primary organizations of the youth league from across the country was given at the Central Youth Hall on the above-said occasion and on the occasion of the 88th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk.  
 Present at the functions were Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, officials of the youth league and youths and students in Pyongyang.

Chinese Ambassador Hosts Reception 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- Wu Donghe, Chinese ambassador to the DPRK, arranged a reception at his embassy Thursday evening in honor of officials of the DPRK Ministry of Foreign Affairs on the occasion of the New Year, Juche 95 (2006).
 Present there on invitation were Minister Paek Nam Sun, Vice-Minister Kim Yong Il and other officials of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs.
 Also present were staff members of the Chinese embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wu in his speech said that the historic meeting between General Secretary Hu Jintao and General Secretary Kim Jong Il during Hu's visit to the DPRK marked an important occasion in deepening and developing the traditional Sino-Korean friendship in the new century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that the Chinese people are sincerely rejoiced over the fact that the fraternal Korean people have achieved great successes on various fronts of socialist construction through their general advance of the Songun revolution under the wise guidance of Kim Jong Il this year and thus celebrated the 60th anniversaries of the Workers' Party of Korea and Korea's liberation in grand style. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He wholeheartedly wished the Korean comrades greater success in the struggle to build a great prosperous powerful nation and achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Paek Nam Sun in his speech said that this year recorded a new chapter in the annals of the DPRK-China friendship as it witnessed the Pyongyang meeting of the top leaders of the two countries and the completion of the Taean Friendship Glass Factory as a symbol of the DPRK-China friendship in the new century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He recalled that this year the fraternal Chinese people have made great progress in the efforts to attain a higher goal of the socialist modernization drive, achieve the complete reunification of the whole country and build a peaceful and prosperous new world under the leadership of the Communist Party of China. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He sincerely wished the Chinese people great success in all fields of socialist construction in 2006, the first year of the 11th five-year plan under the leadership of the CPC with Hu Jintao as its general secretary.

Japan Urged to Take Honest Approach toward Liquidation of Its Past 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- It is quite natural for Japan to remain distrusted by the international community as it does as dictated by the U.S. without its own principle and independence,  it thinks money is everything and is rushing headlong into aggression, far from drawing a lesson from its crime-woven past.
 Rodong Sinmun Friday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan has dreamt of being a permanent member of the UN Security Council at any cost this year, but it has gone bust. It is due to Japan's persistent moves to become a political power and realize its wild ambition for overseas expansion, while shelving the issue of liquidating its past.
 This year, 60 years since the defeat of the Japanese imperialists, witnessed the evermore undisguised moves to incite militarism through the distortion of history and visits to the "Yasukuni Shrine" in Japan. Japan has escalated in real earnest the moves to revise the Constitution in a bid to turn Japan, which has professed to be a "pacifist state," into a war state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The danger of militarization of Japan, a criminal state, and its wild ambition for overseas aggression has further increased this year than ever before. For this reason, the vigilance against Japan and anti-Japanese sentiment have mounted higher than ever before worldwide. There have been widespread signature campaigns against Japan's bid to become a permanent member of the UNSC in different countries of the world including Asian countries. An increasing number of countries clarified their official stands opposing Japan's bid in the international arena. It is the common view and stand of the international community that Japan should not be allowed to sit on that important international body having the heavy responsibility to ensure global peace and security. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's unsuccessful bid to become a permanent member of the UNSC this year proved that this membership can neither be bought nor can be won with the backing of a big country and it can never sit on it unless it gets the confidence of the international community.
If Japan is to gain trust of the international community as its member, it should take an honest attitude and stand towards the issue of liquidating its past and give up its militaristic moves.

Taean Friendship Glass Factory Built on Best Place 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- The Taean Friendship Glass Factory has turned out quality plate glass of hundreds of thousands of square meters in the two months since its commissioning. 
 The success is attributable mainly to the factory's location in the best place in the central part of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is close to the sources of raw materials and consumer areas and has favorable transport conditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The factory, which consumes a hundred and scores of tons of sand a day, transports sand by ship through the West Sea and the River Taedong.
 The railway lines have been laid to its compound. More raw materials needed for the normalization of production will be brought in by rail. It is also linked with motorways leading to all directions of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recently, cargo-ships for carrying 150-ton class trucks started to work between Tami-ri, Taean County and Oryu-dong, Songrim City to make more favorable condition for the operation of the factory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The factory is provided with ample electricity and industrial water as it is situated near Pyongyang with leading power bases and the River Taedong. 
 Chinese technicians who participated in the construction of the factory said as one that it was hard to find such suitable place as Taean for glass factory in other parts of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Now all the production processes of the factory are in normal operation.

Noble Moral Obligation Prevails in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- December 25 is the tenth anniversary of the publication of leader Kim Jong Il's famous work "Respecting the Forerunners of the Revolution Is a Noble Moral Obligation of Revolutionaries".
 The work serves as a historic milestone in paving a new phase for the building of revolutionary morals and a militant banner indicating the way to accomplish the cause of socialism with the revolutionary moral obligation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the last decade noble moral obligation has been displayed to the full in the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A model has been created in the cause of perpetuating the memory of the leader, which has been unprecedented in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The people of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea have built the Kumsusan Memorial Palace as the sacred temple of Juche to have President Kim Il Sung as in his lifetime. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to the embodiment of the slogan "Let us arm ourselves more firmly with the revolutionary idea of the great leader Comrade Kim Il Sung!" in the whole society, the ideas and exploits of the President have been thoroughly defended and brilliantly carried forward. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A social trait of valuing and treating preferentially the elders of the revolution including first and second generations is given to fuller play than ever before and their ideal and aspiration have come true on this land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, the revolutionary spirit and fighting trait of the anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters have been displayed at the construction sites of modern factories and monumental edifices including large-sized land alignment and the Paekma-Cholsan Waterway projects and their lofty life will continue along with the advancing fatherland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the recent years, hero Kim Ki Bong dedicated his life to rescue his comrade from a critical condition, woman So Hye Suk is looking after many orphans and young people are attending war veterans with no kith and kin to depend on. Such lofty moral trait is pervading the whole society to convert the DPRK into a big family of socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All this is the fine fruition of vitality and validity of the ideas advanced by Kim Jong Il in the work.

National Meeting Marks 14th Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Assumption of Office as KPA Supreme Commander
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- A national meeting to mark the 14th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army took place at the April 25 House of Culture on Dec. 23.
 The meeting was attended by Kim Yong Nam, Jo Myong Rok, Pak Pong Ju and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 KPA Vice Marshal Kim Yong Chun who is member of the DPRK National Defence Commission and chief of the KPA General Staff, made a report.
 Kim Jong Il's assumption of supreme commandership of the revolutionary armed forces of the DPRK marked an epochal event of great significance in accomplishing the Juche cause of building the army and developing the Korean revolution and it was the biggest fortune for the army and people of the DPRK, the reporter said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Since early in the 1960s when he started leading the army he has wisely led the cause of building the army holding aloft the banner of the Songun idea which President   Kim Il Sung set out when he was pioneering the Korean revolution and had consistently maintained, thus making a history of a turn in building the revolutionary armed forces of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il, who held the important post of the supreme commander of the KPA according to the unanimous desire and will of the army and people of the DPRK, has brought about a new great turning-point in building the armed forces as required by the Korean revolution which has developed in depth on the basis of the noble exploits and a wealth of experience he has gained in accomplishing the cause of building the army and effected a historic turn in the efforts to raise the position of the army as the core and its leading role in the revolution and construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Underscoring the need for all the servicepersons and people to defend the headquarters of the revolution headed by Kim Jong Il at the cost of their lives and unconditionally implement the party's line and policies, the reporter continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should resolutely defend the immortal Songun revolutionary exploits performed by Kim Jong Il in leading the army and people along the road of victory and eternally glorify them as the eternal cornerstone of our party and the revolution and the best treasure of the nation. 
 All the Party members, servicepersons and people should absolutely trust and follow Kim Jong Il, single-mindedly unite around him to firmly defend the single-minded unity of all the servicepersons and people with the revolutionary headquarters as its core and demonstrate its invincible might.
 We should wage a more vigorous movement for winning the title of O Jung Hup-led 7th Regiment to make the whole army the vanguard devotedly defending the revolutionary headquarters, the first-line human bullets and bombs and thus firmly develop the KPA into a main force, a core unit of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All servicepersons of the KPA should always and sharply follow the enemies' moves with high revolutionary vigilance and keep themselves combat ready to beat back any sudden aggression by them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should give fuller play to the traditional traits of the army-people unity, the foundation of our society. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should, at the same time, firmly adhere to the Party's line of economic construction in the Songun era and direct greater efforts to developing the defence industry on a priority basis so as to bolster our war deterrent for self-defence a thousand times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter called for realizing the three forms of cooperation--national independence, peace against war and reunification and patriotism--under the banner of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration and thus building an independent and prosperous reunified power on this land of three thousand-ri by the concerted efforts of the Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went on to say: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We are still standing in acute confrontation with the imperialist reactionaries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is now keen on economic sanctions and "human rights" racket aimed at overthrowing the system in the DPRK behind the curtain of dialogue.
 We will further increase our military deterrent to defend our system as long as the U.S. continues to pursue its hostile policy toward the DPRK. If the U.S. imperialists provoke a war of aggression at any cost, the army and people of the DPRK will mercilessly wipe out the enemies with the might of Songun to resolutely protect the dignity and sovereignty of the country and the nation.
